                            <comment id="471927" author="adilger" created="Thu, 18 Sep 2025 05:06:11 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The interop testing failure happened because the older client without &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18924&quot; title=&quot;Super big mdt.*.hsm.max_requests will cause system crash.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18924&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18924&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; meets the MDS with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18924&quot; title=&quot;Super big mdt.*.hsm.max_requests will cause system crash.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18924&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18924&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That is what the &lt;tt&gt;sanity-hsm.ex&lt;/tt&gt; check is meant to fix.  The test should only be run if client &amp;gt;= MDS, or MDS &amp;lt;= client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, in one recent failure case the b2_15 client did not have the patches to check the &lt;tt&gt;sanity-hsm.ex&lt;/tt&gt; files.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
